data.name: Maple Glazed Brussels Sprouts
data.quickTastyDescription: Sweet and savory Brussels sprouts that make a perfect side dish!
detailedCookingInstructions: Trim the ends of the Brussels sprouts and remove any yellow leaves. Cut them in half if they are large.
In a large bowl, combine Brussels sprouts with olive oil, maple syrup, salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Toss until well coated.
Spread the Brussels sprouts on a baking sheet in a single layer.
Roast in the oven for 20 minutes, stirring halfway through, until they are golden brown and crispy on the edges.
Remove from the oven and serve warm.
